{"word":"ματεύω","slug":"ματεύω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ματεύω</b></el> <el>(μᾰτεύω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>*<el>μάω</el>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>like <a href='S:μαστεύω'><el>μαστεύω</el></a>,\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to seek, search</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> <i>to seek after, seek for, search after</i>, properly of hounds casting for the scent, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; then generally, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to seek</i> or <i>strive to</i> do, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>4. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> loci, <i>to search, explore</i>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}